      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under version control with documented test suite; all simulation scripts archived and traceable to reported results.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 19.2 used under institutional license with version control. Simulation scripts and mesh files archived in institutional repository with SHA-256 checksums. Automated regression test suite confirms solver build integrity. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate order-of-accuracy convergence on canonical benchmark problems relevant to rotating machinery flows.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent verified against Taylor-Couette flow and lid-driven cavity benchmarks. Observed second-order spatial convergence confirmed. Vendor verification documentation reviewed and accepted for MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for velocity and shear stress quantities of interest; GCI < 5% on fine grid.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on FDA centrifugal pump geometry (coarse: 2.1M, medium: 5.8M, fine: 14.3M cells). GCI for volume-averaged shear stress: 3.2% (fine-to-medium). Richardson extrapolation applied. Discretization error within acceptable bounds for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) must be documented and match simulation boundary conditions within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Five operating points (2–6 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM) replicated from published FDA benchmark experimental protocol. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s) properties matched within 1.2%. Inlet turbulence intensity set to 5% consistent with experimental upstream conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulated velocity fields must agree with PIV measurements within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty; RH index must be within 15% of measured values.",
      "rationale": "Velocity magnitude comparison against FDA PIV data shows mean absolute error of 4.8% across measurement planes. Relative hemolysis index predictions within 11% of experimental values across all five operating points. Systematic over-prediction at high-RPM condition attributed to turbulence model limitations, documented and accepted at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest (volume-averaged shear stress, relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint of pump-induced hemolysis.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate. Volume-averaged scalar shear stress feeds the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model. Both QoIs are established in FDA guidance and ASTM F1841 as appropriate surrogates for pump-induced hemolysis. Direct clinical relevance confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use geometry and operating conditions sufficiently similar to the CPB COU to support extrapolation of model credibility.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump — the same platform as the COU device. Operating conditions span the clinical CPB range. Geometric similarity index > 0.92 between validation and COU configurations. Validation activities are directly relevant to the COU at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence of residuals to solver default tolerances is sufficient at MRL 2 when discretization error is separately assessed.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, explicit quantification of numerical solver error beyond residual monitoring is not required. All simulations converged to residuals below 1e-5 for continuity and momentum. Solver error not separately assessed per MRL 2 scoping; discretization error assessment provides adequate numerical credibility coverage."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, formal use error analysis is not required provided simulation team has documented CFD experience.",
      "rationale": "Simulation team has documented experience with rotating machinery CFD (>5 peer-reviewed publications). Formal use error assessment not required at MRL 2. Team qualifications reviewed and accepted by credibility assessment lead."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, model form uncertainty need not be formally quantified; selection of turbulence model must be documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published performance for confined rotating flows. Formal model form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2. Model selection rationale documented in simulation plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (fluid viscosity, density, pump geometry dimensions) must be traceable to measurements or specifications with stated uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog fluid properties measured at 37°C: density 1050 ± 2 kg/m³, dynamic viscosity 3.5 ± 0.1 mPa·s. Pump geometry digitized from manufacturer drawings with dimensional tolerances ±0.05 mm. All inputs traceable to calibrated measurement records. Input uncertainty propagation performed via ±1 sigma perturbation study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
